WEBVTT

00:09.400 --> 00:12.080
Skirace by Eleanor Jop

00:19.080 --> 00:27.540
It's Sunday. Sue, Rebecca and their friends arrive at their holiday chalet. 

00:25.040 --> 00:30.900
Everybody is very excited. 

00:31.000 --> 00:33.380
They are going to ski.

00:33.960 --> 00:36.600
Sue and Rebecca love skiing. 

00:36.700 --> 00:38.280
They are good at skiing.
   
00:39.940 --> 00:42.880
It's early on Monday morning. 

00:42.980 --> 00:47.280
Everybody is at the ski higher shop. 

00:45.280 --> 00:52.760
Sue and Rebecca are choosing their boots and skis.
   
00:52.860 --> 00:57.120
They put on their boots and carry their skis.
 
00:58.500 --> 01:03.340
Sue has yellow boots and blue skis. 

01:03.440 --> 01:08.620
Rebecca has red boots and white skis.

01:09.660 --> 01:13.800
Sue's poles are sticking out behind her. 

01:13.900 --> 01:17.140
Mark trips over Sue's skis.

01:18.900 --> 01:25.940
Are you okay? Your friends ski poles are in the way. 

01:26.000 --> 01:27.720
You've got big feet.

01:31.540 --> 01:37.680
The snow looks hard. Yes the skiing will be fast today. 

01:37.780 --> 01:41.500
Sue and Rebecca are in the ski lift.
  
01:42.780 --> 01:46.400
The hard snow of the beast is below them. 

01:46.500 --> 01:50.480
The ski lift is taking them to the top of the mountain.
 
01:51.420 --> 01:55.720
They are going to ski down the beast from the top of the mountain.
 
02:01.600 --> 02:06.580
Sue and Rebecca get off the ski lift at the top of the mountain.
 
02:07.600 --> 02:10.680
Then they ski down the mountain. 

02:11.280 --> 02:15.100
They are good skiers. They don't fall over.

02:16.660 --> 02:19.240
David and Mark are watching them. 

02:19.540 --> 02:22.680
David and Mark are also good skiers.

02:26.060 --> 02:30.520
They're good skiers, but we're better.

02:33.700 --> 02:39.560
The young people ski all day. They enjoy themselves.
 
02:40.760 --> 02:45.320
In the evening, they ski back to their chalet.

02:45.400 --> 02:47.260
They are very tired.

02:55.140 --> 02:57.460
It's Wednesday morning. 

02:57.560 --> 03:01.220
The young people are waiting to go up on the ski lift.
 
03:02.480 --> 03:05.080
They are listening to their teacher. 

03:05.180 --> 03:08.580
There's going to be a ski race. 

03:08.680 --> 03:11.280
Sue and Rebecca want to win.
  
03:12.320 --> 03:12.100
David and Mark want to win. 

03:12.200 --> 03:17.480
Everybody wants to win.
 
03:19.420 --> 03:22.900
We're arranging a race on Saturday. 
 
03:22.980 --> 03:24.820
That's the last day of the holiday.

03:26.380 --> 03:29.520
The race is 10 kilometers long. 

03:29.620 --> 03:31.920
It's a long and difficult piece.

03:32.520 --> 03:36.260
Who wants to race? I do. I do.

03:42.840 --> 03:46.380
The young people go up the mountain. 

03:46.480 --> 03:49.060
They put on their skis.

03:49.160 --> 03:51.200
They ski down the beast.
  
03:52.460 --> 03:55.060
They are practicing for the race. 

03:55.160 --> 03:59.660
Sue and Rebecca are skiing fast.

03:59.760 --> 04:01.760
They want to win the race.
 
04:03.380 --> 04:07.500
Mark and David are also skiing fast. 

04:07.600 --> 04:10.380
They want to pass Sue and Rebecca.

04:11.280 --> 04:13.400
But they can't. 

04:13.500 --> 04:19.020
Look at them. They want to win. But we're going to win.

04:19.800 --> 04:23.560
It's difficult. Yes, but it's fun.

04:28.600 --> 04:33.820
It's Saturday morning. Saturday is the last day

04:33.820 --> 04:37.100
of the holiday. It's the day of the

04:37.100 --> 04:37.420
race.

04:38.320 --> 04:43.460
The race is in the afternoon. Sue and

04:43.460 --> 04:44.740
Rebecca are hungry.

04:46.080 --> 04:48.460
They leave their skis at the side of

04:48.460 --> 04:52.420
the cafe. They sit down and order lunch.

04:58.340 --> 05:03.680
I'm hungry. A large hamburger, please. A large

05:03.680 --> 05:06.380
pizza and a large Coke, please.

05:09.360 --> 05:14.480
David and Mark see Sue and Rebecca. They

05:14.480 --> 05:17.100
don't want Sue and Rebecca to win the

05:17.100 --> 05:17.440
race.

05:18.880 --> 05:24.160
They find Rebecca and Sue's skis. They undo

05:24.160 --> 05:27.540
a screw on one of Sue's skis.

05:29.080 --> 05:33.300
These are Sue's blue skis. I'll undo the

05:33.300 --> 05:33.700
binding.

05:34.420 --> 05:39.980
Good. Now the skis won't work. We're sure

05:39.980 --> 05:40.660
to win.

05:47.940 --> 05:53.780
Everybody is ready. The race is starting. Who

05:53.780 --> 05:54.740
is going to win?

05:55.480 --> 05:59.400
Are Sue and Rebecca going to win? Are

05:59.400 --> 06:01.400
David and Mark going to win?

06:03.400 --> 06:07.720
Come on, Sue and Rebecca. Come on, David

06:07.720 --> 06:08.280
and Mark.

06:09.200 --> 06:12.820
On your marks, get set, go.

06:17.500 --> 06:23.140
Sue and Rebecca are in front. Then Sue's

06:23.140 --> 06:24.240
ski comes off.

06:25.140 --> 06:29.540
Sue falls. She slides across the snow and

06:29.540 --> 06:30.740
off the piste.

06:31.640 --> 06:40.160
Rebecca stops to help her. David and Mark

06:40.160 --> 06:52.140
ski past. Mark shouts to David.

06:54.560 --> 07:00.080
Sue and Rebecca repair Sue's ski. Now Sue

07:00.080 --> 07:01.060
can ski again.

07:02.120 --> 07:06.380
They look for the piste. Suddenly they see

07:06.380 --> 07:09.880
the piste. They see the other skiers.

07:13.100 --> 07:15.040
Now they are racing again.

07:28.900 --> 07:33.580
Sue and Rebecca come first. They win the

07:33.580 --> 07:33.960
race.

07:35.220 --> 07:38.920
It's the end of the holiday. Back home

07:38.920 --> 07:43.420
tomorrow. Congratulations Sue and Rebecca.

07:44.340 --> 07:50.260
It's not fair. We are first. We are

07:50.260 --> 07:51.000
the winners.

07:52.140 --> 07:57.220
Well done. Well done. Brilliant.

